news.title: New Zealand home prices dip in August, buyers remain cautious
news.para: New Zealand's housing market experienced a slight dip in August, with median home prices decreasing by 1.3% from July and 0.5% year-on-year, according to REINZ. Despite aggressive interest rate cuts by the Reserve Bank of New Zealand to stimulate the economy, prospective buyers remain cautious. Seasonally adjusted national home sales also fell 4.5% from July, although they were up 0.

news.title: China's home prices extend decline, more policy support needed
news.para: China's housing market continues its decline, with new home prices falling again in August, extending a slump since May 2023. Despite stimulus measures, the sector remains a drag on economic growth. Analysts anticipate further adjustments and call for stronger measures to stabilize the market, including easing restrictions and potential interest rate cuts, as weak demand and economic headwinds persist.

news.title: Delhi civic body launches user-friendly property tax calculator for easy self-assessment
news.para: The Municipal Corporation of Delhi has launched a property tax calculator. Citizens can now calculate their tax independently. The tool is available on the official portal. Users can download a PDF of the calculation. A helpdesk is also available on the website. The 'Suniyo' scheme has generated over Rs 304 crore.

news.title: Signature View residents vacate flats as DDA offers monthly rent aid ahead of demolition
news.para: Following IIT Delhi's assessment deeming Signature View apartments structurally unsafe, the DDA has initiated demolition proceedings. Residents are gradually vacating the premises, aided by monthly rent assistance of Rs 50,000 for three-bedroom and Rs 38,000 for two-bedroom flats.

news.title: Birla Corporation to consolidate operations in cement business
news.para: Birla Corporation Limited, a key player in central India's cement industry with a 20 million tonne capacity, aims to expand to 27.6 million tonnes by 2028-29 with a Rs 4335 crore investment. The company is also exploring diversification opportunities and focusing on its jute business, while increasing its renewable energy consumption to protect its market share and enhance value.

news.title: House prices in UK fall while rents rise by least in four years: Surveys
news.para: Britain's housing market is showing signs of cooling as asking prices for homes dipped 0.1% annually in September, the first decline since January. Rightmove data indicates southern England properties are primarily driving this decrease. Simultaneously, Zoopla reports that average rental price increases have slowed to a four-year low of 2.4%, with monthly rents averaging £1,300.

news.title: Bhopal metro gains ground as it looks to acquire land by consent or via SDM
news.para: Landowners along Bhopal Metro's Orange Line are increasingly embracing the Mutual Purchase Policy, expediting land acquisition through mutual consent and compensation within two months. Forty property owners have already agreed, with compensation for structures and full payment for landowners.

news.title: Allahabad HC orders site inspection of disputed group housing plot in Noida
news.para: The Allahabad High Court has intervened in a dispute between a developer, SDS Housing, and YEIDA. A court commissioner will inspect a contested housing plot in Sector 26. This follows conflicting claims about the land's possession. SDS Housing claims they never received the land despite payments. YEIDA insists possession was transferred.

news.title: Only paying house tax doesn’t make structure legal: GCZMA
news.para: The Goa Coastal Zone Management Authority (GCZMA) has ordered the demolition of illegal structures, including shacks and hotel extensions, on Agonda's turtle nesting beach in Canacona. The GCZMA clarified that paying house tax doesn't legitimize illegal construction. Following a complaint about unlawful constructions in the CRZ area, site inspections confirmed the violations.

news.title: Noida authority to map its land bank, water bodies along expressway
news.para: Noida Authority is set to conduct a detailed topographic survey across key city stretches, including areas along the Yamuna and Noida Expressways, to identify land availability and expand its land bank for future development. This survey will map land surface features, reveal vacant parcels, identify encroachments, and highlight undevelopable areas, aiding in systematic sector planning and preventing ownership disputes.

news.title: Madras HC confirms total ban on resorts and hotels on elephant corridor
news.para: The Madras High Court upheld the ban on commercial activities within the Segur Plateau Elephant Corridor, confirming a Supreme Court committee's findings, including the prohibition of resorts and hotels. Landowners can cultivate eco-friendly crops without barriers.

news.title: Can’t sell regularised houses on Goa government land for 20 years: Draft rules
news.para: Goa government notifies draft rules for regularising houses on government land. Beneficiaries cannot sell or transfer the land for 20 years. Even after 20 years, transfer is subject to government approval. False declarations can lead to jail time or fines. Objections to the rules can be submitted to the revenue secretary. Land must be used only for dwelling purposes.

news.title: L&T keen to exit from Hyderabad metro, cites operational & financial challenges
news.para: Larsen & Toubro (L&T) intends to exit Hyderabad Metro Rail phase I due to operational challenges, financial losses, and complications arising from integrating phase I and II stations under separate administrations. L&T has offered to sell its stake to the state or central government, as the project faces accumulated losses of Rs 6,000 crore and lower-than-expected ridership.

news.title: Easy Home Finance raises long-term funds from Franklin Templeton AIF via NCDs
news.para: Easy Home Finance, backed by Ranjan Pai's Claypond Capital and Sumitomo Mitsui Banking Corporation, has secured long-term financing through NCD issuance with Franklin Templeton AIF. This investment, funded by Franklin India Credit AIF, will fuel Easy's expansion in high-potential housing districts and strengthen its capital base.

news.title: Goa government to have one housing project in each taluka for homeless, poor
news.para: The Goa government is set to launch a housing project in each taluka, prioritizing citizens who cannot afford housing or are homeless. Implemented through the Goa Housing Board, the first project featuring 100 1BHK flats will be in Pernem, allotted on a long-term lease.

news.title: NBCC seeks nod to demolish six more unsafe towers at Green View in Gurugram
news.para: NBCC India Limited seeks permission to demolish more unsafe towers at Green View housing project in Gurugram. The company already razed part of the complex deemed uninhabitable in 2022. They are awaiting DTCP approval to demolish towers A, B, C, D, EWS blocks, a school, shopping complex and an underground tank.

news.title: HC tells Noida authority to supply water to Wish Town flats in two weeks
news.para: The Allahabad High Court directed Noida Authority to provide water connections to Wish Town within two weeks, contingent upon Jaypee Infratech Limited (JIL) submitting a Rs 60 crore bank guarantee. The court also stayed the recovery of Rs 23 crore in disputed charges.

news.title: Rajasthan housing board projects draw huge response in small towns
news.para: Rajasthan Housing Board's new residential schemes in smaller towns and semi-urban areas have seen an overwhelming response. Schemes in Nainwa (Bundi district) and Badi Road (Dholpur) received more applications than available units. The Udaipur scheme, offering 142 flats, witnessed applications 18 times the number of units, indicating strong demand.

news.title: Pune: Deputy CM instructs officials to issue stop-work notices to builders violating regulations
news.para: Pune's guardian minister Ajit Pawar, during a Hadapsar visit, instructed officials to issue stop-work notices to builders flouting civic norms, addressing citizen grievances about poor amenities and infrastructure. He emphasized inter-departmental coordination for traffic management and infrastructure development, suggesting PMRDA might transfer open spaces to PMC.

news.title: Mohali development body warns of FIRs against illegal construction in New Chandigarh
news.para: Gmada has issued a stern warning regarding illegal construction in six New Chandigarh villages, threatening FIRs against violators. This action follows reports of unauthorized building activities, with Gmada emphasizing that prior approval is mandatory for any construction.
